.TH la-toolhive-thv-ui 1 "2026-04-13" "1.0.0" "la-toolhive-thv-ui Manual"

.SH NAME
la-toolhive-thv-ui \- A user UI to start, stop toolhive mcp-optimizer using thv command line

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B la-toolhive-thv-ui
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.B la-toolhive-thv-ui\-tray
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B la-toolhive-thv-ui
is a GUI application for GNOME, Xfce, and KDE desktop environments.
It optionally provides a system tray icon and can be started automatically
on login via XDG autostart or a user systemd service.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/la-toolhive-thv-ui/
Application data directory.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/la-toolhive-thv-ui.desktop
XDG desktop entry (application launcher).
.TP
.I /etc/xdg/autostart/la-toolhive-thv-ui\-tray.desktop
XDG autostart entry for the system tray (all users).
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/user/la-toolhive-thv-ui.service
User systemd service unit. Enable with:
.B systemctl \-\-user enable \-\-now la-toolhive-thv-ui.service

.SH AUTOSTART
The tray component can be started on login in two ways:

.TP
.B XDG autostart (all desktop environments)
Installed to
.I /etc/xdg/autostart/la-toolhive-thv-ui\-tray.desktop
and activated automatically by the desktop environment on login.

.TP
.B systemd user service (systemd-based sessions)
.EX
systemctl --user enable --now la-toolhive-thv-ui.service
.EE

.SH AUTHOR
AUTHOR_NAME <AUTHOR_EMAIL>

